<p itemprop="description">Strategy and planning involves developing long-term direction, setting objectives, analysing environments and options, and creating actionable plans to achieve organisational goals and respond to challenges and opportunities.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand strategic thinking concepts and recognise the importance of planning in achieving organisational objectives. You can contribute to planning activities.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can develop tactical plans, conduct basic environmental analysis, and support strategic planning processes by gathering information and analysing options.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can lead strategic planning processes, conduct comprehensive environmental scanning, develop strategic options, and create detailed implementation plans with clear objectives and measures.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can establish strategic planning methodologies, lead organisation-wide strategic transformation, influence strategic direction at senior levels, and mentor others in strategic thinking.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

